sentences: Jordan Mark Witzigreuter (born November 14, 1989), known professionally as Onlychild and formerly as The Ready Set, is an American singer-songwriter from Fort Wayne, Indiana, United States.
As of July 2019, Witzigreuter has begun a new project, now using the name "Onlychild."

Witzigreuter is also a part of the synthpop band Nekokat, alongside Cameron Walker, and Jess Bowen of The Summer Set.
In 2021, in collaboration with Cameron Walker-Wright, Witzigreuter created the music label Swim Team Records.

Pete Wentz signed Witzigreuter to his label Decaydance Records in 2009.
The song lasted 21 weeks on chart and is certified platinum by RIAA.
The second single More Than Alive was released on May 25, 2010.
I'm Alive, I'm Dreaming, peaked at number 3 on US Top Heatseekers albums chart lasting 23 weeks chart and peaked at number 172 on Billboard Current Album Sales.
On November 2010, his single, Love Like Woe was one of the recipients for the BDS Spin Awards after receiving 50,000 spins.

2012–15: The Bad & The Better =
He released Give Me Your Hand in 2012 which peaked at number 30 on US Mainstream Top 40 and number 33 in New Zealand.
He would serve as an act on Warped Tour in 2014.
In 2015, Witzigreuter started a side project band Nekokat with artist Cameron Walker-Wright and drummer Jess Bowen.
